{
  "text": "Before creating the NAT gateway, we need an Elastic IP address. An Elastic IP is a static, public IP address that you allocate to your awesome count. Unlike regular public IPs that change when instances restart, Elastic IPs persist. The NAT gateway needs this static IP piece persist. The NAT gateway needs this static IP because it acts as the outbound gateway for all private subnet traffic. When instances and private subnets need to reach the internet, their traffic goes through the NAT gateway, which uses this Elastic IP address.",
